<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,428]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,332,356]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was collected on different seashore 
<typeStatus box="[884,943,333,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">types</typeStatus>
in the southern part of Primorsk Territory. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,376,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleji">
<emphasis box="[151,376,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Chersodromia leleji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[592,764,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gamoviensis">
<emphasis box="[592,611,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[626,764,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">gamoviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is distinguished from the latter only in the structure of the male terminalia.
</paragraph>
